  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Message passing is the fundamental mechanism through which agents in a multi-agent system exchange information, delegate tasks, and coordinate behaviour. Rather than sharing mutable state directly, agents communicate through discrete, typed messages \u2014 a discipline that keeps coupling low, makes data flow explicit, and enables parallelism without race conditions."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Message Passing Architecture",
          "title": "Typed messages flow from a Coordinator to worker agents; results are stored and aggregated"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why Typed Messages Matter"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In a LangGraph graph every edge carries data through the shared state dict. Message passing adds a layer of intentional structure on top of that: each node can receive a well-defined envelope that names the sender, the payload type, and any routing metadata. This gives you three practical benefits:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Explicitness"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 the data contract between two agents is captured in a Python dataclass, not inferred from dict keys."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Traceability"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 every message can carry a correlation id, enabling end-to-end spans across async hops."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Parallelism"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 the LangGraph Send API dispatches typed messages to many agents at once, each running in its own thread without touching shared mutable objects."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Designing the Message Schema"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Start by defining the messages your system will exchange. Keep each message focused on a single intent \u2014 task assignment, result reporting, or status notification. Using Python dataclasses keeps the schema readable and provides free type-checking via mypy."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Any, Literal\nimport uuid\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass TaskMessage:\n    \"\"\"Sent from coordinator to a worker agent.\"\"\"\n    task_id: str = field(default_factory=lambda: str(uuid.uuid4()))\n    task_type: str = \"\"           # e.g. \"research\", \"analyse\", \"summarise\"\n    payload: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)\n    priority: int = 0             # higher = more urgent\n    sender: str = \"coordinator\"\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass ResultMessage:\n    \"\"\"Sent from a worker back to the coordinator or message store.\"\"\"\n    task_id: str = \"\"\n    agent_id: str = \"\"\n    status: Literal[\"ok\", \"error\", \"partial\"] = \"ok\"\n    result: Any = None\n    error: str | None = None\n    tokens_used: int = 0\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass StatusMessage:\n    \"\"\"Heartbeat or progress update.\"\"\"\n    agent_id: str = \"\"\n    progress: float = 0.0   # 0.0\u20131.0\n    note: str = \"\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "State Schema with Annotated Reducers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Because multiple agents can emit ResultMessages simultaneously, use the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "operator.add"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " reducer on the result list so parallel writes are appended rather than overwritten:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import operator\nfrom typing import Annotated\nfrom typing_extensions import TypedDict\n\n\nclass MultiAgentState(TypedDict):\n    # Outbound task queue \u2014 coordinator writes here\n    tasks: list[TaskMessage]\n    # Results accumulate safely across parallel agents\n    results: Annotated[list[ResultMessage], operator.add]\n    # Status heartbeats\n    status_log: Annotated[list[StatusMessage], operator.add]\n    # Final synthesised answer\n    final_answer: str\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Building the Graph"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The coordinator node reads the task list from state, creates one "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Send"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " per task addressed to the appropriate worker, then returns. Each worker node receives its "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "TaskMessage"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " through the Send payload and appends a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "ResultMessage"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to state."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from langgraph.graph import StateGraph, END\nfrom langgraph.constants import Send\nfrom langchain_anthropic import ChatAnthropic\n\nROUTING: dict[str, str] = {\n    \"research\": \"research_agent\",\n    \"analyse\": \"analysis_agent\",\n    \"summarise\": \"synthesis_agent\",\n}\n\n\ndef coordinator(state: MultiAgentState) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Fan out tasks to workers via Send.\"\"\"\n    sends = [\n        Send(ROUTING[task.task_type], {\"task\": task})\n        for task in state[\"tasks\"]\n        if task.task_type in ROUTING\n    ]\n    return sends  # LangGraph dispatches each Send in parallel\n\n\ndef make_worker(agent_id: str, system_prompt: str):\n    llm = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\")\n\n    def worker(state: dict) -> dict:\n        task: TaskMessage = state[\"task\"]\n        try:\n            response = llm.invoke([\n                {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": system_prompt},\n                {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": str(task.payload)},\n            ])\n            msg = ResultMessage(\n                task_id=task.task_id,\n                agent_id=agent_id,\n                status=\"ok\",\n                result=response.content,\n                tokens_used=response.usage_metadata[\"total_tokens\"],\n            )\n        except Exception as exc:\n            msg = ResultMessage(\n                task_id=task.task_id,\n                agent_id=agent_id,\n                status=\"error\",\n                error=str(exc),\n            )\n        return {\"results\": [msg]}\n\n    return worker\n\n\ndef synthesiser(state: MultiAgentState) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Merge results into a final answer.\"\"\"\n    ok_results = [r for r in state[\"results\"] if r.status == \"ok\"]\n    combined = \"\\n\\n\".join(str(r.result) for r in ok_results)\n    llm = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-sonnet-5\")\n    answer = llm.invoke([\n        {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"Synthesise the following agent outputs into one coherent answer.\"},\n        {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": combined},\n    ])\n    return {\"final_answer\": answer.content}\n\n\nbuilder = StateGraph(MultiAgentState)\nbuilder.add_node(\"coordinator\", coordinator)\nbuilder.add_node(\"research_agent\", make_worker(\"research_agent\", \"You are a research specialist.\"))\nbuilder.add_node(\"analysis_agent\", make_worker(\"analysis_agent\", \"You are a data analysis specialist.\"))\nbuilder.add_node(\"synthesis_agent\", make_worker(\"synthesis_agent\", \"You are a synthesis specialist.\"))\nbuilder.add_node(\"synthesiser\", synthesiser)\n\nbuilder.set_entry_point(\"coordinator\")\n# After all workers, converge on synthesiser\nfor worker in [\"research_agent\", \"analysis_agent\", \"synthesis_agent\"]:\n    builder.add_edge(worker, \"synthesiser\")\nbuilder.add_edge(\"synthesiser\", END)\n\ngraph = builder.compile()\n"
          }
        ]
      },
