      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM-Decided Routing"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When the task type is ambiguous, let a lightweight model classify it. Constrain the output to agent names to prevent hallucinated destinations:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from langchain_anthropic import ChatAnthropic\nfrom langchain_core.output_parsers import StrOutputParser\nfrom langgraph.constants import Send\n\nAGENT_NAMES = [\"research_agent\", \"analysis_agent\", \"synthesis_agent\"]\n\n_router_llm = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\")\n\n\ndef llm_coordinator(state: MultiAgentState) -> list[Send]:\n    sends = []\n    for task in state[\"tasks\"]:\n        prompt = (\n            f\"Task description: {task.payload.get('description', '')}\\n\"\n            f\"Choose exactly one agent: {', '.join(AGENT_NAMES)}\\n\"\n            \"Reply with the agent name only.\"\n        )\n        agent_name = (\n            _router_llm\n            | StrOutputParser()\n        ).invoke(prompt).strip()\n\n        if agent_name not in AGENT_NAMES:\n            agent_name = \"research_agent\"  # safe fallback\n\n        sends.append(Send(agent_name, {\"task\": task}))\n    return sends\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Error Handling and Dead-Letter Queue"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Workers fail. When a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "ResultMessage"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " arrives with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "status=\"error\""
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", the synthesiser must decide whether to retry with another agent, degrade gracefully, or surface the failure. A simple retry pattern uses a counter in the message:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "@dataclass\nclass TaskMessage:\n    task_id: str = field(default_factory=lambda: str(uuid.uuid4()))\n    task_type: str = \"\"\n    payload: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)\n    priority: int = 0\n    sender: str = \"coordinator\"\n    retry_count: int = 0        # incremented on each retry\n    max_retries: int = 2\n\n\nclass DeadLetterState(TypedDict):\n    tasks: list[TaskMessage]\n    results: Annotated[list[ResultMessage], operator.add]\n    dead_letters: Annotated[list[TaskMessage], operator.add]\n    final_answer: str\n\n\ndef retry_router(state: DeadLetterState):\n    \"\"\"After workers finish, retry failed tasks or move to dead-letter.\"\"\"\n    failed_task_ids = {\n        r.task_id for r in state[\"results\"] if r.status == \"error\"\n    }\n    task_by_id = {t.task_id: t for t in state[\"tasks\"]}\n\n    sends = []\n    dead = []\n    for tid in failed_task_ids:\n        task = task_by_id.get(tid)\n        if task and task.retry_count < task.max_retries:\n            retried = TaskMessage(\n                **{k: v for k, v in task.__dict__.items() if k != \"retry_count\"},\n                retry_count=task.retry_count + 1,\n            )\n            sends.append(Send(ROUTING[retried.task_type], {\"task\": retried}))\n        elif task:\n            dead.append(task)\n\n    if dead:\n        return {\"dead_letters\": dead}\n    return sends  # re-dispatch retries\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Observability: Correlation IDs and Tracing"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A correlation id threads through the entire message chain so you can reconstruct the causal graph in LangSmith or your own log pipeline. Include it on every message and propagate it to the LLM call's metadata:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import uuid\nfrom langchain_core.callbacks import LangChainTracer\nfrom langchain_core.runnables import RunnableConfig\n\n\ndef make_traced_worker(agent_id: str, system_prompt: str):\n    llm = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\")\n\n    def worker(state: dict, config: RunnableConfig) -> dict:\n        task: TaskMessage = state[\"task\"]\n        # propagate correlation id as a LangSmith run tag\n        run_config = {\n            **config,\n            \"run_name\": f\"{agent_id}/{task.task_id[:8]}\",\n            \"tags\": [f\"task_id:{task.task_id}\", f\"agent:{agent_id}\"],\n        }\n        response = llm.invoke(\n            [{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": system_prompt},\n             {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": str(task.payload)}],\n            config=run_config,\n        )\n        return {\n            \"results\": [ResultMessage(\n                task_id=task.task_id,\n                agent_id=agent_id,\n                status=\"ok\",\n                result=response.content,\n                tokens_used=response.usage_metadata[\"total_tokens\"],\n            )]\n        }\n\n    return worker\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Operational Considerations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Message size"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 LangGraph state is serialised to the checkpoint store on every step. Keep payloads small; reference large artefacts by ID and retrieve them inside the worker."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Ordering"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 parallel Send dispatches run concurrently and may finish out of order. If downstream synthesis depends on ordered results, include a sequence number in the TaskMessage and sort in the synthesiser."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
